title: Which subset of V=(3) is not equal to V? - Quora

response.answer_text: I assume you mean that VV is the set whose only element is the number 3,3, so standard notation would use braces (or sometimes we say “curly braces”) like this: V=3V=3. If so, VV has two subsets: the empty set ∅∅ and VV itself. The subset that isn’t VV is then the empty set ∅∅
